Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, then remove the cores from the @bell pepper{1} and cut into 1cm wide slices. Halve, peel and finely chop the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped). Roughly chop the @coriander{5}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Spread the @yellow pepper{1}(halved, cored and sliced) and @green pepper{1}(halved, cored and sliced) out on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a little @olive oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{ground}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and a little crispy round the edges, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> If the peppers are done before you're finished with everything else, just take them out of your oven to wait, then pop them back in to warm though for a couple of minutes before serving.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add the onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes}, until soft. Add the mixed beans, @ground cumin{1.32%tsp}, a small pinch of @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp}, @tomato puree{15%g} and @water{100%ml}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{ground}. Cook with the #lid{} on for ~{15%minutes}, until the beans start to break down.

Zest the @lime{1/2} with a #grater{}. Stir a pinch of the zest into the @soured cream{75%g} then squeeze a little juice in too. Not too much! Add a little @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Stir it all together, check that you like the level of seasoning and adjust if necessary. Keep to one side.

To make the refried beans remove one half of the bean mixture to a #bowl{}. Mash the rest in the pan to a paste using the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}. Add back the reserved beans along with half the coriander. Taste and add a little more salt if necessary.

Put the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} in your oven to warm for ~{2%minutes} (heat up the peppers at this stage too if necessary). Toss the @wild rocket{40%g} in a little leftover lime juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{} and some @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Serve the peppers, refried beans, citrus sour cream, rocket and remaining coriander in separate bowls so everyone can dive in and create their own fajitas. Enjoy!